==English==
===Etymology===
From the Greek ''γύρος'' (pronounced [ˈʝiros]), meaning ''turning''.

===Pronunciation===
In sense 1 often pronounced ['giro] or ['yiro] after the Greek, but often pronounced ['ʤaɪɹoʊ] after sense 2; in sense 2 always pronounced ['ʤaɪɹoʊ] or similar.

